metadata.name: Organic Oeuvre #19
metadata.description:
First project on FXHash.

Entirely coded in p5js.

Stochastic strokes while ensuring randomness is consistent; uses 500+ color palettes.

The pieces created by this project are dynamic and change based on the size of the viewing window ("organic"), making each viewing experience unique. 

In case you find a bug, please consider it an easter egg! Write to me on twitter if you think it's a bug and I'll send another couple your way from my reserved :)

Press s to save the image in fullscreen.

metadata.name: ZOOM (4hwf) #81
metadata.description:
"Das System lässt keine Überraschung zu. Überraschung ist Ausdruck partieller Unkenntnis. Überraschung weist auf Mangel von Wissen hin, deutet Leerstellen an. Bisher hatten sie keine Leerstellen festgestellt." — Herbert W. Franke

ZOOM explores linear scaling of pixels by zooming into a noisy framebuffer. Various zoom levels are composed one below the other, becoming a cinematic animation through iteration of the hue values of the pixels in the framebuffer.

In Gedenken an Herbert W. Franke
Kim Asendorf, 2022

metadata.name: Henoheno Samurai #2518
metadata.description:
This work was inspired by Otsu-e(大津絵), a Japanese painting in the Edo period. Otsu-e were inexpensive paintings made as souvenirs. Although mass-produced using paper stencils, the artisans painted by hand, resulting in variations in the quality of their work. Connoisseurs found them interesting and collected them as works of art. Otsu-e showed a new value of beauty in Japanese art, different from Ukiyo-e (浮世絵) which are prints, and from fine art paintings which are one-of-a-kind artworks.

This work is made of canvas2D Bezier curves. Not just a combination of parts, but also a random displacement of the Bezier curve points to lose the shape. This is intended to create fun with the Otsu-e-like effect.


Features:
This profile is made up of 8 parts (brows, eyes, nose, mouth, ear, contour, hair, and body). Each part has 100 basic types. 
There are 7 skin colors and 12 kimono colors. Each RGB value of the colors is randomly added within a range of ±10. In addition, there are 70 kimono patterns. 
The distortion rate due to displacement of Bezier curve points is 0.0~50.0. 


BTW The title "Henoheno" is taken from the Japanese character picture "Henohenomoheji" known since the Edo period.

metadata.name: Metamorphosis #145
metadata.description:
This project uses cellular automata where the state of a cell in a new generation is determined based on its own and its neighbors' states in the previous generation. The guiding rules for these transitions, however, are not static; they undergo a random change every few generations, chosen from a possible 256 rules. By also slightly shifting the positions of cells and using an outline and texture that conveys a hand-drawn style, I have tried introducing an element of organic randomness.

Stepping away from the monochromatic color scheme used in my last three series, I have used a gradient effect to convey a transitioning hue across generations, combining a palette of two colors selected from an array of 14 different palettes. 

Note on the name: The alternating rules and fluctuating cell positions serve as the apparent justification for its name. However, a subtler inspiration lies in my deep admiration for Franz Kafka and his remarkable short story, "The Metamorphosis". Kafka’s narrative explores the constantly evolving state of human existence, where patterns appear momentarily only to dissipate quickly. Just when you think you've spotted a pattern, poof, it changes. Just like in life, right :)

Implemented in JS, this code utilizes the Perlin.js and Simple-noise.js libraries.

Press p to save a png of the image in full screen. Press s to save an svg file. 

Pixel Love!

metadata.name: Badgirs City #24
metadata.description:
"I used to live in a small city placed at the center of Iran's plateau with the warmest summer days in the country part; spending most of my childhood with my sweet grandma at her old house. She was always keeping her eyes on me not to get heat stroke at noon playing in the yard when the sun was at its peak glowing furiously. Sundays at noon were my favorite, I used to call them “Ice cream” noons sitting beside the nicest person you could imagine and enjoying a delightful ice cream. You won't know how lovely it was to have an ice cream relaxing under the most enjoyable cold breeze of the tallest windcatcher in the city at her house. "



The Badgirs city is the first collaboration between Fleep and IceRain on Fxhash. The concept was established first with the design of a school with a feeling of safe and nostalgia reminding us of the good memories of our childhood as the grandma’s house and the windcatcher for Fleep.
A windcatcher (Badgir) is an Iranian traditional architectural element in the form of a small tower built on the roof of houses in warm locations to create passive cooling. The collection of Badgirs city is a modern recreational development of those traditional windcatchers designed by Fleep and icerain and exquisitely translated into code by Icerain.

Controls:
[1] Set the resolution to Medium Resolution
[2] Set the resolution to High Resolution

metadata.name: Cybergoonies #13
metadata.description:
Greetings, fellow cybernauts and inhabitants of the blue planet! Allow us to introduce Cybergoonies a generative PFP project collaboration between the visionary artist Ayra Mularama and creative code writer radarboy3000. This project serves as the inaugural fundraising effort for Crypto Art Week Asia, which promotes artists in Asia and curates and produces events to celebrate Asia as a rising creative force in the digital art and crypto scene and the convergence of art and technology in the digital realm.

By supporting the Cybergoonies project, not only can users create their own one-of-a-kind PFPs, but they can also contribute to the growth and development of the crypto art community. So come on and join us in this exciting journey into the digital frontier!

512 PFPs. 2750x4889.

https://www.cryptoartweekasia.com/
https://aryamularama.com/
https://radarboy3000.com

metadata.name: Curtains #59
metadata.description:
Curtains

While learning more about flow fields, as an intermediate step, the first version of this came out.
The artwork creates a set of lines; the first point of the lines are anchors, which can be in a straight line, sinus wave, or tangent function.
The second point is set by calculating the angle from the first using Perlin noise.

The project features 10 different hand-picked color schemes.

Actions:
--------------
Press [s] to save
--------------


Created using p5.js

metadata.name: Sandscapes #10
metadata.description:
Sandscapes generates multiple scenarios drawn with a random mix of colors with a noise reinterpretation.

Outputs are diverse with a common mist ambient, transporting the viewer to different environments such as sand dunes, red sunsets, purple sunrises, mountains, rivers, skin texture, or simply an elegant background with a unique mix of colors.

--
Sandscapes genera multiples escenarios dibujados con una mezcla aleatoria de colores y una reinterpretación con ruido.

Las imágenes son diversas con un ambiente de neblina común, y trasladan al espectador a diferentes entornos tales como dunas de arena, rojos atardeceres, violetas amaneceres, montañas, rios, textura de piel, o sencillamente un elegante background con una mezcla de colores única.

metadata.name: Here, After #379
metadata.description:
We were all there
when the sky cried confetti
and if we weren’t, we felt like we had
but here, after
held with each other’s eyes
not much is said at all

——

A : Animate rendering
S : Save current resolution
1 -> 5 : Save low -> high resolution

metadata.name: Tumble Down Light Factory #416
metadata.description:
Tumble Down Light Factory is an interpretation of light installations & murals.

It attempts to trigger the feeling of coming up on a new block in a new city to discover an unexpected piece of art that is stories tall or entering a new room, knowing there will be a projection dominating the space with its light and color.

This is an abstract distillation of those things and those feelings.

Each composition is initially drawn to a hidden “template” canvas which is sampled and then rendered on the main canvas in various ways after applying some transforms to give it some depth (and so you can actually see it.)

Viewing in full-screen is nice. You should try it.

T : Save hidden ‘template’ image
S : Save current resolution
1 -> 5 : Save low -> high resolution
